{
  "doc_id": "13353",
  "text": "The role of sustained participation in physical activity (PA) throughout the life-course provides some of the best prospects for ageing well [CITATION_1] . Regular PA has been shown to reduce the risk of chronic diseases such as ischaemic heart disease, hypertension, type 2 diabetes, osteoporosis, some cancers, and depression [CITATION_2] . Maintaining a PA lifestyle has also been shown to reduce the risk of all-cause mortality [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . A growing body of evidence is developing regarding the cognitive benefits of sustained PA in older people as well as improved quality of sleep, health-related quality of life, and lower risk of falls [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
